- Vault: Def Leppard Greatest Hits (as described) is a tightly sequenced, radio‑ready hits collection with glossy, vocal‑forward mixes, immediate sing‑along choruses, lush layered harmonies, concise track lengths and steady upbeat energy. While the emphatic sing‑along choruses and layered harmonies overlap with my secondary interest in arena energy, the emphasis on concise, hook‑driven, front‑of‑mix vocals and steady upbeat energy points toward an immediate, uniform pop/rock hit compilation. That aligns less well with my preference for subtle dynamics, extended instrumental passages, and piano/acoustic textures; it also risks the kind of hook‑driven uniformity I noted as a dislike when it sacrifices nuance for immediacy.
