Evaluation and rationale:
- Candidate 1 explicitly emphasizes lush strings, choir layers and dense multi‑part harmonies, inventive studio sequencing, wide dynamics and meticulous mastering, plus clear pressing/mastering credits, coherent two‑disc sequencing and polished packaging. Those features map very closely to multiple stated preferences: layered instrumentation and subtle dynamics that reward attentive, start‑to‑finish listening; cinematic, expansive arrangements that satisfy my taste for richly produced theatrical/prog material; and the importance I place on well‑documented, well‑mastered physical releases (pressing/mastering credits and polished packaging). The presence of inventive sequencing and coherent two‑disc sequencing aligns with my liking for albums that are designed to be listened to as a whole (as in my Supertramp reference). The emphasis on lush orchestration and dense harmonies also matches my preference for production detail and repeated plays revealing new things.
