- Collectability and sequencing: Exhaustive liner/mastering credits and collectible packaging are explicitly present and encourage cohesive front‑to‑back listening — this satisfies my archival/collector preference and the desire for narrative album sequencing that rewards uninterrupted listening.
Why I reject the AOR remaster (All the Best)
- Missing primary axis (piano/keys‑forward): The AOR remaster description centers on a close, upfront lead and economical arrangements but does not promise piano/key leadership. My primary criterion is piano/keys‑forward records; since the AOR release does not offer that, it fails my top priority.
